<br>
Read what I actually say, before responding, thx.<br>
<br>
The person that taught me to shoot a bow has been doing it most of his life. He hunts for his own food with a bow. The arrows he uses, are designed to go through the animal and cause very little pain. The animal may feel something, but it will only last maybe a few seconds. Just an example, a bear is running along, someone shoots it with an arrow, arrow goes through the bear, bear may feel something, but most likely it will just keep running then fall over dead shortly after. Bow and arrow is a more humane way of hunting then a gun.<br>
