<br>
The facts out of the way, I am a meat hunter (not a sportsman, there is a profound difference), however I choose not to bow hunt.  The skill required to execute what is an ethical shot, one which I am certain will fell the animal, exceeds what I am capable of producing with sufficient confidence.  My weapon and means of choice is to still hunt whitetail deer with a 12 gauge shotgun, #4 buckshot, if you must know.<br>
<br>
Reach up and feel the sharp incisors in your mouth - if it was not for those sad additions to the gene pool that were hunters, you simply would not be here today.<br>
<br>
So yes, speaking of ignorance, you chimed in on cue.<br>
